{"id":"joash","term":"Joash","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Whom Jehovah bestowed. (1.) A contracted form of Jehoash, the father of Gideon (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 6:11\">Judg. 6:11</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:29\">29</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 8:13\">8:13</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 9:7\">29</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 9:10\">32</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) One of the Benjamite archers who joined David at Ziklag (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 12:3\">1 Chr. 12:3</a>).</p>\n<p>(3.) One of King Ahab’s sons (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 22:26\">1 Kings 22:26</a>).</p>\n<p>(4.) King of Judah (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 11:2\">2 Kings 11:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 12:19\">12:19</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 12:20\">20</a>). (See JEHOASH [1].)</p>\n<p>(5.) King of Israel (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 13:9\">2 Kings 13:9</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 13:12\">12</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 13:13\">13</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 13:25\">25</a>). (See JEHOASH [2].)</p>\n<p>(6.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 7:8\">1 Chr. 7:8</a>.</p>\n<p>(7.) One who had charge of the royal stores of oil under David and Solomon (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 27:28\">1 Chr. 27:28</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Judges 6:11","Genesis 1:29","Genesis 8:13","Genesis 9:7","Genesis 9:10","1 Chronicles 12:3","1 Kings 22:26","2 Kings 11:2","2 Kings 12:19","2 Kings 12:20","2 Kings 13:9","2 Kings 13:12","2 Kings 13:13","2 Kings 13:25","1 Chronicles 7:8","1 Chronicles 27:28"]}